6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 732, L.D. 1113, “An Act Regarding
10 Fairness in Sentencing for Persons Under 26 Years of Age”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act Regarding Fairness in Sentencing for Persons Based on Age'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 17-A MRSA §1602, sub-§1, ¶B, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 113, Pt. A, §2,
16 is amended to read:
17 B. Second, the court shall determine the maximum term of imprisonment to be
18 imposed by considering all other relevant sentencing factors, both aggravating and
19 mitigating, appropriate to the case. Relevant sentencing factors include, but are not
20 limited to, the character of the individual, the age of the individual at the time the
21 conduct forming the basis for the conviction occurred, the individual's criminal history,
22 the effect of the offense on the victim and the protection of the public interest.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment requires that
2277 when sentencing an individual for a Class A, Class B or Class C crime, the court consider
2288 the age of the individual at the time the conduct forming the basis for the conviction
2299 occurred, in addition to the other sentencing factors considered by the court.
